Pre-Game Insights: The Togolese national football team will face a significant challenge in their upcoming matches against Algeria, scheduled for October 10 and 14, 2024, as their starting goalkeeper, Jeffrey Agboloso, will be absent due to ankle surgery.
Jeffrey Agboloso, a key player for Togo, was injured during training and had been a crucial part of the team in previous qualification matches against Liberia and Equatorial Guinea.
The Togolese team is currently preparing in Tunisia and will travel to Annaba, Algeria, to face the Algerian team.
The absence of Agboloso could impact the dynamics of the game, as he had shown great determination and impressive skills in previous matches.
The Togolese Football Federation is considering alternative solutions to replace Agboloso, hoping that this situation will not disrupt the team's performance.
